Somehow I gained weight somewhere in my 20s, and due to excessive working-out, and a very forward-oriented personality (I already have a PHD), I found myself in a bigger mess of “I’m pretty, but not quite pretty enough…that would get you beautiful girls, and isn’t that what I want? However, if I don’t spend more time studying I won’t get that degree, though without that I’ll never make more money, which would at least guarantee me one day a regular job in my field. And finally, a regular job would also give me a broader address-book of prospects, etc, etc. All these should matter to me. But not quite. I should probably get some more sleep and finish these rather than wasting my time writing this.

Um, great site, though. And fantastic questions!

I’m currently living in Taiwan, and it is exceptionally difficult to send pictures of me to the rest of the world for photoshopping. I have already checked. If you guys ever create an branch in Asia, let me know!
